<subSubSection id="C37C653EFFFF1B26FF0C6FFEE534DDDD" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD936B5FFFF1B26FF0C6FFEE534DDDD" blockId="2.[151,1437,968,2003]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">
<emphasis id="B912EAA7FFFF1B26FF0C6FFEE571DD05" bold="true" box="[199,308,1256,1282]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Remarks</emphasis>
. (1) In the original description, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B44FFFF1B26FD566FFEE77ADD04" author="Walker, F." box="[669,831,1256,1283]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" refId="ref3873" refString="Walker, F. (1865) List of the Specimens of Lepidopterous Insects in the Collection of the British Museum, Part 32. Supplement. Part 2. Trustees of the British Museum, London, 323 - 706." type="book" year="1865">Walker (1865)</bibRefCitation>
did not mention a number of specimens therefore the existence of 
<typeStatus id="54DD8817FFFF1B26FEE96E1BE5C1DD20" box="[290,388,1293,1319]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">syntypes</typeStatus>
is possible. In order to stabilize the nomenclature, we hereby designate the specimen deposited in OUMNH (
<figureCitation id="135D2A30FFFF1B26FEF86E26E538DD4D" box="[307,381,1328,1354]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[165,1426,181,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[155,1432,179,1883]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Arcilasisa sobria: adults. Depositories of the specimens: 1 in OUMNH; 2–4 in ZSM; 5–8 in TAAHU." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521546/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="135D2A30FFFF1B26FE456E26E5D8DD4D" box="[398,413,1328,1354]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[210,1357,194,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[210,1376,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9–11. Arcilasisa sobria: male genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 9 in OUMNH; 10 and 11 in TAAHU." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521548/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">9</figureCitation>
) as 
<typeStatus id="54DD8817FFFF1B26FE1A6E26E67EDD4D" box="[465,571,1328,1354]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">lectotype</typeStatus>
. (2) The type locality of the species provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B44FFFF1B26FBB56E26E166DD4C" author="Walker, F." box="[1150,1315,1328,1355]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" refId="ref3873" refString="Walker, F. (1865) List of the Specimens of Lepidopterous Insects in the Collection of the British Museum, Part 32. Supplement. Part 2. Trustees of the British Museum, London, 323 - 706." type="book" year="1865">Walker (1865)</bibRefCitation>
as “South Hindostan” is doubtful since it inhabits high mountain regions and all the more recently collected Indian specimens originate from the Himalayan part of the country. (3) The male genital capsules of the specimens dissected display a variability in the length of the cucullus and the width of the digitus (
<figureCitation id="135D2A30FFFF1B26FC626E8AE05EDDB1" box="[937,1051,1436,1462]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 9–11" captionStart-1="FIGURES 12–13" captionStartId-0="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionStartId-1="5.[151,264,1082,1106]" captionTargetBox-0="[210,1357,194,1902]" captionTargetBox-1="[167,1418,181,1048]" captionTargetId-0="figure-19@4.[210,1376,181,1919]" captionTargetId-1="figure-19@5.[159,1427,181,1058]" captionTargetPageId-0="4" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionText-0="FIGURES 9–11. Arcilasisa sobria: male genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 9 in OUMNH; 10 and 11 in TAAHU." captionText-1="FIGURES 12–13. Arcilasisa sobria: male (12) and female (13) genitalia. The specimens dissected are deposited in TAAHU." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521548" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521550" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6521548/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6521550/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Figs 9–12</figureCitation>
) which was also seen in a number of 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D36FFFF1B26FF7D6ED6E557DDDD" box="[182,274,1472,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Apamea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B912EAA7FFFF1B26FF7D6ED6E557DDDD" box="[182,274,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Apamea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37C653EFFFF1B26FF0C6EF2E6ABDDF8" box="[199,750,1508,1535]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD936B5FFFF1B26FF0C6EF2E6ABDDF8" blockId="2.[151,1437,968,2003]" box="[199,750,1508,1535]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">
